---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionDivider from '@components/SectionDivider.astro';
import Callout from '@components/Callout.astro';
import ResourceCard from '@components/ResourceCard.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Community"
  description="Connect with the Iraqi Social Progress Collective via encrypted XMPP messaging. No phone number required, no digital footprint, fully private."
  lang={lang}
  articleWidth
>
  <section class="prose">
    <SectionDivider />
    <h1>Community</h1>

    <p>
      We use the <strong>XMPP</strong> protocol to connect with our community. If
      you have not heard of it, do not worry — we will walk you through it step by step.
    </p>

    <hr />
    <h2>What is XMPP?</h2>

    <p>XMPP is an open-source messaging protocol with these properties:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Encrypted.</strong> Messages are end-to-end encrypted with OMEMO. Only you and the recipient can read them.</li>
      <li><strong>Decentralized.</strong> No single company owns it, and no single government can shut it down.</li>
      <li><strong>Federated.</strong> Like email — you create your account on any server, and you can talk to people on other servers.</li>
      <li><strong>No phone number required.</strong> Unlike WhatsApp or Telegram, XMPP does not need your phone number or your real identity.</li>
      <li><strong>Open source.</strong> Anyone can audit the code. There is no hidden surveillance.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />
    <h2>Setup steps</h2>

    <h3>1. Install the Conversations app</h3>

    <p>
      Conversations is the best XMPP app for Android. You can download it for
      free from the F-Droid store (no Google account needed):
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="https://f-droid.org/en/packages/eu.siacs.conversations/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Download Conversations from F-Droid
      </a>
    </p>

    <p>
      F-Droid is a free, open-source app store. If you do not have it yet,
      install it first from <a href="https://f-droid.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">f-droid.org</a>.
      For iPhone users, the closest alternative is <strong>Monal</strong> (available on the App Store).
    </p>

    <h3>2. Register a free account</h3>

    <p>
      When you open the app for the first time, choose "Create new account".
      You can register on one of these free public servers:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>conversations.im</strong> — the official Conversations server.</li>
      <li><strong>jabber.de</strong> — a trusted free German server.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Choose a username that does not reveal your identity. Do not use your real
      name, nickname, or birthdate. Pick something unrelated to you.
    </p>

    <hr />
    <h2>Contact us</h2>

    <p>Once you have your account, you can reach us in one of two ways:</p>

    <h3>XMPP</h3>
    <p>Add the following JID to your contacts:</p>
    <p><code class="bg-navy/5 px-2 py-1 font-mono text-sm">iriszimmerfrau@conversations.im</code></p>

    <h3>ProtonMail</h3>
    <p>If you prefer encrypted email:</p>
    <p><code class="bg-navy/5 px-2 py-1 font-mono text-sm">iriszimmerfrau@proton.me</code></p>

    <hr />
    <h2>What to expect when you reach out</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>We usually respond within 48 hours.</li>
      <li>We will not ask for your real name or location unless it is necessary to help you.</li>
      <li>We will not share your information with anyone — ever.</li>
      <li>You can write in Arabic, English, or Kurdish.</li>
      <li>If we cannot help directly, we will try to point you to a trusted resource.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />
    <h2>Anonymous contribution</h2>

    <p>
      Do you have a story or experience you want to share with the community? You
      can do so completely anonymously.
    </p>

    <h3>How to share your story</h3>

    <ol>
      <li>Create a new XMPP account with a pseudonym unrelated to you (follow the steps above).</li>
      <li>Message us at <code class="bg-navy/5 px-2 py-1 font-mono text-sm">iriszimmerfrau@conversations.im</code> and let us know you would like to share your story.</li>
      <li>Write your story however you want — formal or colloquial, long or short.</li>
      <li>We will review it with you and remove any details that might identify you before publishing.</li>
      <li>We will never publish anything without your explicit consent.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>
      Your voice matters, and your story may help someone else who feels alone.
      Share it if you want to, in the way that works for you.
    </p>

    <!-- ===== External Resources ===== -->
    <hr />
    <h2 id="external-resources">External community resources</h2>

    <Callout type="warning">
      These are <strong>external community spaces, not run by ISPC</strong>. We
      list them because Iraqi queer people gather there — but each platform
      collects different data about you, and what you post there is outside our
      protection. Read each platform's warning below before joining.
      <strong>Use a VPN. Never use your real name, real phone number, or any
      photo that could identify you. Create a fresh pseudonymous account that you
      have never used elsewhere.</strong>
    </Callout>

    <h3>Discord</h3>
    <p>
      Discord requires phone verification on many servers — <strong>this can leak
      your Iraqi phone number to Discord and, in past breaches, to other users</strong>.
      Use a virtual / non-Iraqi number if possible. Messages persist indefinitely
      on Discord's servers. Voice chat reveals your voice. Profile pictures are
      visible to every server member. If you join, use an account you have never
      used elsewhere.
    </p>
    <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 my-4">
      <ResourceCard
        platform="Discord"
        url="https://discord.gg/hCwyVwFB"
        title="Iraqi queer community server"
        description="One of three operator-listed Discord servers gathering queer Iraqis. ISPC does not moderate this server."
      />
      <ResourceCard
        platform="Discord"
        url="https://discord.gg/mazVfWbd7u"
        title="Iraqi queer community server"
        description="One of three operator-listed Discord servers gathering queer Iraqis. ISPC does not moderate this server."
      />
      <ResourceCard
        platform="Discord"
        url="https://discord.gg/2hfjUDBAy"
        title="Iraqi queer community server"
        description="One of three operator-listed Discord servers gathering queer Iraqis. ISPC does not moderate this server."
      />
    </div>

    <h3>Reddit</h3>
    <p>
      Reddit logs your IP address. Your full comment and voting history is
      <strong>publicly archived</strong> — including by third parties that mirror
      Reddit. An account you have used elsewhere can be cross-referenced against
      anything you say there. Create a fresh throwaway account behind a VPN,
      never link it to any account that knows your real identity, and never post
      anything you would not want surfaced years later.
    </p>
    <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 my-4">
      <ResourceCard
        platform="Reddit"
        url="https://www.reddit.com/r/iraqpride/"
        title="r/iraqpride"
        description="Iraqi pride subreddit — discussion, support, and shared experiences. Posts and comments are publicly archived."
      />
    </div>

    <h3>YouTube</h3>
    <p>
      Watching does not require an account, but <strong>commenting, liking, or
      subscribing requires a Google account</strong> — and Google logs every
      signed-in watch against your real identity. Watch logged out, or in a
      private / incognito window behind a VPN, if you want to keep your watch
      history out of your Google profile. Do not comment from any account tied
      to your real identity.
    </p>
    <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 my-4">
      <ResourceCard
        platform="YouTube"
        url="https://www.youtube.com/@ZFVelvetIris"
        title="@ZFVelvetIris (channel)"
        description="Iraqi queer creator. Videos in Arabic and English on identity, family, and survival."
      />
      <ResourceCard
        platform="YouTube"
        url="https://youtu.be/6pK6ocmt6ZI"
        title="Featured video"
        description="Selected video from @ZFVelvetIris."
      />
      <ResourceCard
        platform="YouTube"
        url="https://youtu.be/VtwTQYLHK1A"
        title="Featured video"
        description="Selected video from @ZFVelvetIris."
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
